article.headline: Norfolk State 34, Liberty 17
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Sam Lawson returned a fumble 5 yards for a touchdown and Norfolk State turned three Liberty miscues into touchdowns to win 34-17 Saturday in the season finale for both teams. A fumble recovery also led to Daryl Jones' 1-yard touchdown run in the first quarter, and Dustin Johnson intercepted a Brock Smith pass that led to Monte Anthony's 13-yard touchdown run in the fourth. Smith was 9-for-28 for 217 yards and three interceptions. The Flames lost three fumbles. Dominic Bolden put Liberty (1-10) ahead when he caught a 21-yard touchdown pass from Smith early in the first quarter. But Norfolk State (4-7) answered with Jones' scoring run and a 42-yard touchdown pass from Brandon Brooks to Derrick Baker to finish the first quarter 14-7. The Spartans stretched the lead to 10 before the break on Lawson's fumble recovery. Greiser's 2-yard touchdown run brought the Flames to within 27-17 with 5:25 remaining, but Norfolk State followed with a 14-yard touchdown run from Terrell Johnson with 45 seconds left. Brooks finished 10-for-21 for 114 yards. Liberty was playing its last game under football coach Ken Karcher, who was fired this week by the school's chancellor and founder, the Rev. Jerry Falwell. The school's athletics director also resigned, and two associate athletics directors were fired.
